cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with resource allocation in cognitive radio networks, which involves the use of wireless communication protocols and techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with optimization and decision-making, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the management of limited resources, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
